comment:
* Provides details on why an IMS call failed. Applications can use the methods in this class to
 * get local or network fault behind an IMS services failure. For example, if the code is
 * CODE_CALL_BARRED, then the call was blocked by network call barring configuration and it is not
 * the device's bug and the user can retry the call when network lift the barring.
 * Typical use case includes call backs when IMS call state changed with this class as a param
 * containing details on why IMS call changed state/failed.

variables.name: CODE_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: * The Reason is unspecified.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_ILLEGAL_ARGUMENT
variables.comment: * The passed argument is invalid.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_ILLEGAL_STATE
variables.comment: * The operation was invoked while in an invalid call state.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_INTERNAL_ERROR
variables.comment: * IMS service internal error

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_IMS_SERVICE_DOWN
variables.comment: * ImsService has crashed (service connection is lost).

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_NO_PENDING_CALL
variables.comment: * No pending incoming call exists

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_ENDED_BY_CONFERENCE_MERGE
variables.comment: * IMS Call ended during conference merge process

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_POWER_OFF
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; radio power off

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_LOW_BATTERY
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; low battery

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_NETWORK_NO_SERVICE
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; out of service (data service state)

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_NETWORK_NO_LTE_COVERAGE
variables.comment:
* Service unavailable; no LTE coverage
     * (VoLTE is not supported even though IMS is registered)

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_NETWORK_ROAMING
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; located in roaming area

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_NETWORK_IP_CHANGED
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; IP changed

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; for an unspecified reason

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_NOT_REGISTERED
variables.comment: * Service unavailable; IMS is not registered

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_EXCEEDED
variables.comment: * Maximum number of simultaneous calls exceeded

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_BUSY
variables.comment: * The call is busy.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_DECLINE
variables.comment: * The Call has been declined locally on this device.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_VCC_ON_PROGRESSING
variables.comment: * Can not complete call; an SRVCC is in progress.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_RESOURCE_RESERVATION_FAILED
variables.comment: * Can not complete call; resource reservation is failed (QoS precondition)

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_CS_RETRY_REQUIRED
variables.comment:
* VoLTE service can't be provided by the network or remote end, retry the call.
     * Resolve the extra code provided in (EXTRA_CODE_CALL_RETRY_*) if the below code is set

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_VOLTE_RETRY_REQUIRED
variables.comment: * VoLTE service can't be provided by the network temporarily, retry the call.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_CALL_TERMINATED
variables.comment: * IMS call is already terminated (in TERMINATED state).

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_HO_NOT_FEASIBLE
variables.comment: * Call was disconnected because a handover is not feasible due to network conditions.

variables.name: CODE_LOCAL_IMS_NOT_SUPPORTED_ON_DEVICE
variables.comment:
* This device does not support IMS.
     * @hide

variables.name: CODE_TIMEOUT_1XX_WAITING
variables.comment: * 1xx waiting timer is expired after sending INVITE request (MO calls only)

variables.name: CODE_TIMEOUT_NO_ANSWER
variables.comment:
* User didn't answer during call setup operation (MO/MT)
     * MO : 200 OK to INVITE request is not received,
     * MT : No action from user after alerting the call

variables.name: CODE_TIMEOUT_NO_ANSWER_CALL_UPDATE
variables.comment:
* User no answer during call update operation (MO/MT)
     * MO : 200 OK to re-INVITE request is not received,
     * MT : No action from user after alerting the call

variables.name: CODE_CALL_BARRED
variables.comment: * The call was blocked by call barring configuration.

variables.name: CODE_FDN_BLOCKED
variables.comment: * The operation is restricted to fixed dialing numbers only.

variables.name: CODE_IMEI_NOT_ACCEPTED
variables.comment:
* Network rejected the emergency call request because IMEI was used as identification
     * and this capability is not supported by the network.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_MODIFIED_TO_USSD
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified DIAL request to USSD request.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_MODIFIED_TO_SS
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified DIAL request to SS request.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_MODIFIED_TO_DIAL
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified DIAL request to DIAL with modified data.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_MODIFIED_TO_DIAL_VIDEO
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified DIAL request to Video DIAL request.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_VIDEO_MODIFIED_TO_DIAL
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified Video DIAL request to DIAL request.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_VIDEO_MODIFIED_TO_DIAL_VIDEO
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified Video DIAL request to Video DIAL request.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_VIDEO_MODIFIED_TO_SS
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified Video DIAL request to SS request.

variables.name: CODE_DIAL_VIDEO_MODIFIED_TO_USSD
variables.comment: * Stk Call Control modified Video DIAL request to USSD request.

variables.name: CODE_SIP_REDIRECTED
variables.comment: * SIP 3xx response: SIP request is redirected

variables.name: CODE_SIP_BAD_REQUEST
variables.comment: * Sip 400 response : Bad Request

variables.name: CODE_SIP_FORBIDDEN
variables.comment: * Sip 403 response : Forbidden

variables.name: CODE_SIP_NOT_FOUND
variables.comment: * Sip 404 response : Not Found

variables.name: CODE_SIP_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment:
* Not supported, because of one of the following:
     * SIP response 415 : Unsupported Media Type,
     * SIP response 416 : Unsupported URI Scheme,
     * SIP response 420 : Bad Extension

variables.name: CODE_SIP_REQUEST_TIMEOUT
variables.comment: * SIP response 408 : Request Timeout.

variables.name: CODE_SIP_TEMPRARILY_UNAVAILABLE
variables.comment: * SIP response 480 : Temporarily Unavailable

variables.name: CODE_SIP_BAD_ADDRESS
variables.comment: * SIP response 484 : Address Incomplete

variables.name: CODE_SIP_BUSY
variables.comment:
* Returned a busy response, may be one of the following:
     * SIP response 486 : Busy Here,
     * SIP response 600 : Busy Everywhere

variables.name: CODE_SIP_REQUEST_CANCELLED
variables.comment: * SIP response 487 : Request Terminated

variables.name: CODE_SIP_NOT_ACCEPTABLE
variables.comment:
* Received a not acceptable response, will be one of the following:
     * SIP response 406 : Not Acceptable
     * SIP response 488 : Not Acceptable Here
     * SIP response 606 : Not Acceptable

variables.name: CODE_SIP_NOT_REACHABLE
variables.comment:
* Received a not acceptable response, will be one of the following:
     * SIP response 410 : Gone
     * SIP response 604 : Does Not Exist Anywhere

variables.name: CODE_SIP_CLIENT_ERROR
variables.comment: * Received another unspecified error SIP response from the client.

variables.name: CODE_SIP_TRANSACTION_DOES_NOT_EXIST
variables.comment: * SIP response 481: Transaction Does Not Exist

variables.name: CODE_SIP_SERVER_INTERNAL_ERROR
variables.comment: * SIP response 501 : Server Internal Error

variables.name: CODE_SIP_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE
variables.comment: * SIP response 503 : Service Unavailable

variables.name: CODE_SIP_SERVER_TIMEOUT
variables.comment: * SIP response 504 : Server Time-out

variables.name: CODE_SIP_SERVER_ERROR
variables.comment: * Received an unspecified SIP server error response.

variables.name: CODE_SIP_USER_REJECTED
variables.comment: * 603 : Decline

variables.name: CODE_SIP_GLOBAL_ERROR
variables.comment: * Unspecified 6xx error.

variables.name: CODE_EMERGENCY_TEMP_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* Emergency call failed in the modem with a temporary fail cause and should be redialed on this
     * slot.

variables.name: CODE_EMERGENCY_PERM_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* Emergency call failed in the modem with a permanent fail cause and should not be redialed on
     * this slot. If there are any other slots available for emergency calling, try those.

variables.name: CODE_SIP_USER_MARKED_UNWANTED
variables.comment:
* Call failure code during hangup/reject if user marked the call as unwanted.
     *
     * Android Telephony will receive information whether ROBO call feature is supported by the
     * network from modem and propagate the same to AOSP as new ImsCallProfile members. OEMs can
     * check this information and provide an option to the user to mark the call as unwanted.

variables.name: CODE_SIP_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 405
     * Method not allowed for the address in the Request URI

variables.name: CODE_SIP_PROXY_AUTHENTICATION_REQUIRED
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 407
     * The request requires user authentication

variables.name: CODE_SIP_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 413
     * Request body too large

variables.name: CODE_SIP_REQUEST_URI_TOO_LARGE
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 414
     * Request-URI too large

variables.name: CODE_SIP_EXTENSION_REQUIRED
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 421
     * Specific extension is required, which is not present in the HEADER

variables.name: CODE_SIP_INTERVAL_TOO_BRIEF
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 422
     * The session expiration field too small

variables.name: CODE_SIP_CALL_OR_TRANS_DOES_NOT_EXIST
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 481
     * Request received by the server does not match any dialog or transaction

variables.name: CODE_SIP_LOOP_DETECTED
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 482
     * Server has detected a loop

variables.name: CODE_SIP_TOO_MANY_HOPS
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 483
     * Max-Forwards value reached

variables.name: CODE_SIP_AMBIGUOUS
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 485
     * Request-URI is ambiguous
     *

variables.name: CODE_SIP_REQUEST_PENDING
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 491
     * Server has pending request for same dialog

variables.name: CODE_SIP_UNDECIPHERABLE
variables.comment:
* SIP Response : 493
     * The request cannot be decrypted by recipient

variables.name: CODE_MEDIA_INIT_FAILED
variables.comment: * Media resource initialization failed

variables.name: CODE_MEDIA_NO_DATA
variables.comment: * RTP timeout (no audio / video traffic in the session)

variables.name: CODE_MEDIA_NOT_ACCEPTABLE
variables.comment: * Media is not supported; so dropped the call

variables.name: CODE_MEDIA_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: * Unspecified media related error.

variables.name: CODE_USER_TERMINATED
variables.comment: * User triggers the call to be terminated.

variables.name: CODE_USER_NOANSWER
variables.comment: * No action was taken while an incoming call was ringing.

variables.name: CODE_USER_IGNORE
variables.comment: * User ignored an incoming call.

variables.name: CODE_USER_DECLINE
variables.comment: * User declined an incoming call.

variables.name: CODE_LOW_BATTERY
variables.comment: * Device declined/ended a call due to a low battery condition.

variables.name: CODE_BLACKLISTED_CALL_ID
variables.comment: * Device declined a call due to a blacklisted caller ID.

variables.name: CODE_USER_TERMINATED_BY_REMOTE
variables.comment: * The call has been terminated by the network or remote user.

variables.name: CODE_USER_REJECTED_SESSION_MODIFICATION
variables.comment:
* Upgrade Downgrade request rejected by
    * Remote user if the request is MO initiated
    * Local user if the request is MT initiated

variables.name: CODE_USER_CANCELLED_SESSION_MODIFICATION
variables.comment: * Upgrade Downgrade request cancelled by the user who initiated it

variables.name: CODE_SESSION_MODIFICATION_FAILED
variables.comment:
* UPGRADE DOWNGRADE operation failed
     * This can happen due to failure from SIP/RTP/SDP generation or a Call end is
     * triggered/received while Reinvite is in progress.

variables.name: CODE_UT_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * UT is currently not supported on this device.

variables.name: CODE_UT_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE
variables.comment: * UT services are currently not available on this device.

variables.name: CODE_UT_OPERATION_NOT_ALLOWED
variables.comment: * The requested UT operation is not allowed.

variables.name: CODE_UT_NETWORK_ERROR
variables.comment: * The UT request resulted in a network error.

variables.name: CODE_UT_CB_PASSWORD_MISMATCH
variables.comment: * The password entered for UT operations does not match the stored password.

variables.name: CODE_UT_SS_MODIFIED_TO_DIAL
variables.comment: * Sim Toolkit Call Control modified the UT operation to a dial command.

variables.name: CODE_UT_SS_MODIFIED_TO_USSD
variables.comment: * Sim Toolkit Call Control modified the UT operation to a USSD command.

variables.name: CODE_UT_SS_MODIFIED_TO_SS
variables.comment: * Sim Toolkit Call Control modified the UT operation to another supplementary service command.

variables.name: CODE_UT_SS_MODIFIED_TO_DIAL_VIDEO
variables.comment: * Sim Toolkit Call Control modified the UT operation to a video call dial command.

variables.name: CODE_ECBM_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Emergency callback mode is not supported.

variables.name: CODE_MULTIENDPOINT_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Fail code used to indicate that Multi-endpoint is not supported by the IMS framework.

variables.name: CODE_REGISTRATION_ERROR
variables.comment: * IMS Registration error code

variables.name: CODE_ANSWERED_ELSEWHERE
variables.comment: * MT call has ended due to a release from the network because the call was answered elsewhere.

variables.name: CODE_CALL_PULL_OUT_OF_SYNC
variables.comment: * For MultiEndpoint - Call Pull request has failed.

variables.name: CODE_CALL_END_CAUSE_CALL_PULL
variables.comment: * For MultiEndpoint - Call has been pulled from primary to secondary.

variables.name: CODE_CALL_DROP_IWLAN_TO_LTE_UNAVAILABLE
variables.comment:
* CALL DROP error code for the case when a device is ePDG capable and when the user is on an
     * active wifi call and at the edge of coverage and there is no qualified LTE network available
     * to handover the call to. We get a handover NOT_TRIGERRED message from the modem. This error
     * code is received as part of the handover message.

variables.name: CODE_REJECTED_ELSEWHERE
variables.comment: * For MultiEndPoint - Call was rejected elsewhere

variables.name: CODE_SUPP_SVC_FAILED
variables.comment: * Supplementary Services (HOLD/RESUME) - the command failed.

variables.name: CODE_SUPP_SVC_CANCELLED
variables.comment: * Supplementary Services (HOLD/RESUME) - the command was cancelled.

variables.name: CODE_SUPP_SVC_REINVITE_COLLISION
variables.comment: * Supplementary Services (HOLD/RESUME) - the command resulted in a re-invite collision.

variables.name: CODE_IWLAN_DPD_FAILURE
variables.comment: * DPD Procedure received no response or send failed.

variables.name: CODE_EPDG_TUNNEL_ESTABLISH_FAILURE
variables.comment: * Establishment of the ePDG Tunnel Failed.

variables.name: CODE_EPDG_TUNNEL_REKEY_FAILURE
variables.comment: * Re-keying of the ePDG Tunnel Failed; may not always result in teardown.

variables.name: CODE_EPDG_TUNNEL_LOST_CONNECTION
variables.comment: * Connection to the packet gateway is lost.

variables.name: CODE_MAXIMUM_NUMBER_OF_CALLS_REACHED
variables.comment:
* The maximum number of calls allowed has been reached.  Used in a multi-endpoint scenario
     * where the number of calls across all connected devices has reached the maximum.

variables.name: CODE_REMOTE_CALL_DECLINE
variables.comment:
* Similar to {@link #CODE_LOCAL_CALL_DECLINE}, except indicates that a remote device has
     * declined the call.  Used in a multi-endpoint scenario where a remote device declined an
     * incoming call.

variables.name: CODE_DATA_LIMIT_REACHED
variables.comment: * Indicates the call was disconnected due to the user reaching their data limit.

variables.name: CODE_DATA_DISABLED
variables.comment: * Indicates the call was disconnected due to the user disabling cellular data.

variables.name: CODE_WIFI_LOST
variables.comment: * Indicates a call was disconnected due to loss of wifi signal.

variables.name: CODE_IKEV2_AUTH_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* Indicates the registration attempt on IWLAN failed due to IKEv2 authetication failure
     * during tunnel establishment.

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_OFF
variables.comment: The call cannot be established because RADIO is OFF

variables.name: CODE_NO_VALID_SIM
variables.comment: The call cannot be established because of no valid SIM

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_INTERNAL_ERROR
variables.comment: The failure is due internal error at modem

variables.name: CODE_NETWORK_RESP_TIMEOUT
variables.comment: The failure is due to UE timer expired while waiting for a response from network

variables.name: CODE_NETWORK_REJECT
variables.comment: The failure is due to explicit reject from network

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_ACCESS_FAILURE
variables.comment: The failure is due to radio access failure. ex. RACH failure

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_LINK_FAILURE
variables.comment: Call/IMS registration failed/dropped because of a RLF

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_LINK_LOST
variables.comment: Call/IMS registration failed/dropped because of radio link lost

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_UPLINK_FAILURE
variables.comment: The call Call/IMS registration failed because of a radio uplink issue

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_SETUP_FAILURE
variables.comment: Call failed because of a RRC connection setup failure

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_RELEASE_NORMAL
variables.comment: Call failed/dropped because of RRC connection release from NW

variables.name: CODE_RADIO_RELEASE_ABNORMAL
variables.comment: Call failed/dropped because of RRC abnormally released by modem/network

variables.name: CODE_ACCESS_CLASS_BLOCKED
variables.comment: Call failed because of access class barring

variables.name: CODE_NETWORK_DETACH
variables.comment: Call/IMS registration is failed/dropped because of a network detach

variables.name: CODE_SIP_ALTERNATE_EMERGENCY_CALL
variables.comment:
* Call failed due to SIP code 380 (Alternative Service response) while dialing an "undetected
     * emergency number".  This scenario is important in some regions where the carrier network will
     * identify other non-emergency help numbers (e.g. mountain rescue) when attempting to dial.

variables.name: CODE_UNOBTAINABLE_NUMBER
variables.comment:
* Call failed because of unobtainable number
     * @hide

variables.name: CODE_NO_CSFB_IN_CS_ROAM
variables.comment:
* Call failed because WiFi call could not complete and circuit switch silent redial
     * is not allowed while roaming on another network.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_UNKNOWN
variables.comment:
* The rejection cause is not known. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_CALL_WAITING_DISABLED
variables.comment:
* Ongoing call, and call waiting is disabled. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_CALL_ON_OTHER_SUB
variables.comment:
* A call is ongoing on another sub. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_1X_COLLISION
variables.comment:
* CDMA call collision. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_SERVICE_NOT_REGISTERED
variables.comment:
* IMS is not registered for service yet. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_CALL_TYPE_NOT_ALLOWED
variables.comment:
* The call type is not allowed on the current RAT. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_E911_CALL
variables.comment:
* And emergency call is ongoing. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_CALL_SETUP
variables.comment:
* Another call is in the process of being establilshed. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_MAX_CALL_LIMIT_REACHED
variables.comment:
* Maximum number of allowed calls are already in progress. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_UNSUPPORTED_SIP_HEADERS
variables.comment:
* Invalid/unsupported SIP headers received. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_UNSUPPORTED_SDP_HEADERS
variables.comment:
* Invalid/unsupported SDP headers received. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_CALL_TRANSFER
variables.comment:
* A call transfer is in progress. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_INTERNAL_ERROR
variables.comment:
* An internal error occured while processing the call. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_QOS_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* Call failure due to lack of dedicated bearer. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_HANDOVER
variables.comment:
* A call handover is in progress. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_VT_TTY_NOT_ALLOWED
variables.comment:
* Video calling not supported with TTY. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_CALL_UPGRADE
variables.comment:
* A call upgrade is in progress. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_CONFERENCE_TTY_NOT_ALLOWED
variables.comment:
* Call from conference server, when TTY mode is ON. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_CONFERENCE_CALL
variables.comment:
* A conference call is ongoing. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_VT_AVPF_NOT_ALLOWED
variables.comment:
* A video call with AVPF is not supported. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_ENCRYPTED_CALL
variables.comment:
* And encrypted call is ongoing; other calls not supported. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_REJECT_ONGOING_CS_CALL
variables.comment:
* A CS call is ongoing. *

* Used with implicit call rejection.

variables.name: CODE_EMERGENCY_CALL_OVER_WFC_NOT_AVAILABLE
variables.comment:
* An attempt was made to place an emergency call over WFC when emergency services is not
     * currently available in the current location.
     * @hide

variables.name: CODE_WFC_SERVICE_NOT_AVAILABLE_IN_THIS_LOCATION
variables.comment:
* Indicates that WiFi calling service is not available in the current location.
     * @hide

variables.name: CODE_RETRY_ON_IMS_WITHOUT_RTT
variables.comment:
* The dialed RTT call should be retried without RTT
     * @hide

variables.name: CODE_OEM_CAUSE_1
variables.comment:
* OEM specific error codes. To be used by OEMs when they don't want to reveal error code which
     * would be replaced by ERROR_UNSPECIFIED.

variables.name: EXTRA_MSG_SERVICE_NOT_AUTHORIZED
variables.comment:
* Network string error messages.
     * mExtraMessage may have these values.
     * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_CODE_CALL_RETRY_NORMAL
variables.comment:
* An extra that may be populated when the {@link #CODE_LOCAL_CALL_CS_RETRY_REQUIRED} result has * been returned. *

* Try to connect the call using CS

variables.name: EXTRA_CODE_CALL_RETRY_SILENT_REDIAL
variables.comment:
* An extra that may be populated when the {@link #CODE_LOCAL_CALL_CS_RETRY_REQUIRED} result has * been returned. *

* Try to connect the call using CS and do not notify the user.

variables.name: EXTRA_CODE_CALL_RETRY_BY_SETTINGS
variables.comment:
* An extra that may be populated when the {@link #CODE_LOCAL_CALL_CS_RETRY_REQUIRED} result has * been returned. *

* Try to connect the call using CS by using the settings.
